  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. This model has been applied in clinical research settings to evaluate absolute hemolysis levels under ventricular assist device operating conditions. Model Risk Level 5 drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite gaps, the assessment team accepted the model for the stated engineering use based on conservative bounding assumptions and sensitivity analysis results.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-prediction-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-flowfield-dataset"
  ],
